Peru Stocks: La Cima, Minera IRL Decline, Candente Copper Climbs

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-06-24T21:54:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/peru-stocks-la-cima-minera-irl-decline-candente-copper-climbs.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 5:18 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 0.1 percent to 18,996.88. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index retreated 0.4 percent to 2,456.17.  Gold and silver producers dropped as a pledge by European
Union leaders to stabilize the regionâ€™s economy cut demand for
precious metals as a haven.  Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAC1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields
Ltd., fell 2.4 percent to 4.10 soles, the lowest in eight weeks.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, declined 3.8 percent to $1.02.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a silver
producer, slid 2.4 percent to 37.30 soles.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)   gained as copper rose in New
York after a bigger-than-forecast rise in orders for U.S.
durable goods revived prospects for manufacturing and metals
demand. The Canadian mining exploration company with operations
in Peru rose for the second time in eight days, advancing 1.6
percent to $1.27.  To contact the reporter on this story:
